Subject: Re: [T2] Rear Break adjuster

On Sun, 30 Mar 2003, Steve Pribyl wrote:

> I was ajusting the rear breaks today and found the adjusters still and
> almost frozen.  A quick spirt of screw loosener set them free.  Took em
> out and cleaned them.   However, they were still a bit stiff when I went
> to adjust them again.
>
> What is the proper grease,if any, to use in this location?

Since we don't want them to sieze up, anti-sieze grease seems to be the
logical choice.  It works for me, and the only time the adjusters come out
is when changing rear brake shoes.

Be really careful of the little springs that hold the stars in place.  If
you break them it's and adventure to fix!

George Lyle
